OpenJML supersedes ESC/Java2, which is no longer maintained.

The paper "OpenJML: JML for Java 7 by extending OpenJDK" by David R. Cok says:
"OpenJML is a re-implementation, on a completely new code-base, of tools such as the JML2 tools for JML on Java 1.4 (including jmldoc and jmlrac) and ESC/Java2 and ESC/Java for static checking."

There is an assignment about using ESC/Java from 2008 here:
https://www.cs.cmu.edu/~aldrich/courses/654-sp08/homework/asst5.pdf

===========================================================================

