ESC/Java version 1.2:

Download escjava-1.2.4-linux.tar.Z and escjava-specs-1.2.4-unix.tar.Z from
  http://crl.research.compaq.com/downloads/download.cgi/mernst@lcs.mit.edu/Compaq+ESC+for+Java/
(Follow, don't right-click on, the ".Z" file links.  Also, cookies must be
enabled.)

Installation instructions at http://research.compaq.com/SRC/esc/download.html

mv escjava-1.2.4-linux.tar.Z escjava-specs-1.2.4-unix.tar.Z ~/java/esc
cd ~/java/esc
tar zxf escjava-1.2.4-linux.tar.Z
(cd escjava; tar zxf ../escjava-specs-1.2.4-unix.tar.Z)
# Compare previous version of specs to new version of specs, and copy over
# any changes.  In particular, copy over Arrays.spec.
ln -s ~/java/esc/escjava/bin/* ~/bin/Linux-i686
# Change top of escjava/bin/escjava to the following:
#   setenv ESCJAVA_ROOT /g2/users/mernst/java/esc/escjava
#   setenv JAVA /g2/users/mernst/java/jdk/bin/java
#   setenv JAVA_STDLIB /g2/users/mernst/java/jdk/jre/lib/rt.jar
# Just below that, make this edit:
#   setenv ESCJ_STDARGS "-suggest -nowarn Deadlock"

# Try it out (should see 5 warnings, I think?):
cd escjava/examples/0.0
escjava Bag.java

===========================================================================

ESC/Java notes:
 * also_requires may be used only on a method implenting an interface
 * requires and ensures only go on the first implementation of a
   method; they are prohibited if overriding a method (whether
   that method is ESC-specified or not)
 * also_modifies may be used on any (overriding) method
 * also_ensures may be used on any (overriding) method
